System Testing
System testing is the execution of the software in its final configuration, including
integration with other software and hardware systems.
System testing is conducted by the programmer who writes the code.
It is a type of blackbox testing.

Acceptance Testing
User Acceptance Testing is the final test before the customer signs-off and accepts it.
User Acceptance Testing is conducted by the end users of the software. They can be the customers themselves or the customer's customers.
It is a type of blackbox testing